{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "For the management of adverse reactions, the dose can be reduced based on individual safety and tolerability, as described in Table 1 of the SmPC.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_e2dd75bdb504", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_e078e06a"}
{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "KISQALI is not recommended to be used in combination with tamoxifen.1", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_86371c8061f2", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_eff0ab58"}
{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "Safety: The most frequent adverse reactions reported in the INBRIJA® clinical studies were cough (15.6%), fall (8.7%), upper respiratory tract infection (5.8%), dyskinesia (5.7%) and sputum discoloured (2.8%). Serious adverse reactions of allergic oedema have been reported with levodopa medicinal products but not in clinical studies with INBRIJA®. Gastrointestinal haemorrhage has been reported with levodopa medicinal products and was observed once in INBRIJA® clinical studies.1", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_ce98a97e20bb", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_8caf08d5"}
{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "Summary of KESIMPTA’s safety profile:", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_88661000e506", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_0fbc1d13"}
{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "The most frequently reported adverse reactions are upper respiratory tract infections (17.1%) (most frequently nasopharyngitis, rhinitis).3 Please see the Summary of Product Characteristics for full details.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_c6d146b71a19", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_27d2db1c"}
{"kind": "text", "role": "SAFETY", "text": "The most important and frequently reported AEs are URTIs (39.4%), SIRRs (20.6%), ISRs (10.9%) and UTIs (11.9%).1", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.2, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_88661000e506", "pattern_id": "uk_email_safety_44fb721e"}
