{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A Venn diagram showing the overlap between ADHD and Autism, highlighting shared characteristics such as family history and early childhood onset pervasive symptoms across situations and sleeping difficulties.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_4ce64e928887", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_2c6a3b9d", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [302.25, 579.0, 522.75, 820.5]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A flowchart showing a four-stage ADHD management pathway: Building Foundation in Primary Care, Upskilling, Advancing, and Implementing Skills. It illustrates progression from initial ADHD patient management through educational training, clinical decision-making support (with CADHU and Activate platforms highlighted), to prescriber engagement and skill implementation.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_4ce64e928887", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_ba7cfcb1", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [77.25, 478.5, 297.75, 570.75]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A progression visual showing Day 0 as the starting point, with clinical or dermatological images displaying skin condition changes. The images appear to show progression of a treatment effect over time, with microscopic or close-up photography of skin appearance.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_ab5138dc3652", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_37e5e25a", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [101.25, 272.25, 498.75, 355.5]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A stylized infographic showing three human figures in silhouette against a black background. One figure is rendered in gray/white on the left, while two figures on the right are rendered in red/crimson, visually representing a ratio or proportion between groups.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_e2dd75bdb504", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_d28ae6f8", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": "https://www.health.novartis.co.uk/medicines/haematology/scemblix/unmet-need", "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [75.0, 400.5, 300.0, 503.25]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A text-based infographic comparing dose modification rates between SCEMBLIX® (asciminib) and bosutinib in Ph+ CP-CML patients. It states that patients taking SCEMBLIX® required fewer dose modifications (42.3%, n=66) compared to bosutinib (61.8%, n=47), with a call-to-action to contact Novartis.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_e2dd75bdb504", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_0a216451", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [75.0, 660.0, 525.0, 779.25]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "A text-based infographic presenting information about Chronic Myeloid Leukaemia (CML) patients on ≥3 line therapy, their association with low 8-year survival, and the reasons for treatment switching due to resistance and tolerability issues with ATP-competitive Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitors.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_e2dd75bdb504", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_34f016ae", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [75.0, 260.25, 525.0, 400.5]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "An animated diagram showing synaptic mechanisms with labels for dopaminergic and noradrenergic pathways, DAT, NET, D1 and α2 receptors, and atomoxetine. Dr. Giovanni Giaroli is presenting the psychopharmacology of ADHD medications.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_4ce64e928887", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_b3cee5ec", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [75.0, 854.25, 525.0, 1099.5]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "An arrow-shaped infographic displaying a percentage reduction in risk. The visual shows '34% minder risico op progressie of overlijden' (34% lower risk of progression or death) compared to eBEACOPP, with accompanying statistical data (HR 0.66; 95% CI 0.45-0.97; p=0.035).", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_915f5ab39161", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_fe63f025", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": "https://takedapro.nl/node/737?customer_id=NL-TAK-P-0012400000d68qMAAQ&utm_source=smile&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=breacadd_continu&utm_term=fragmentvae&utm_content=hd21", "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [84.0, 382.5, 274.5, 535.5]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "An infographic displaying a 28% reduction in treatment-related morbidity (TRMB) compared to eBEACOPP, with statistical details showing a relative risk of 0.72 (95% CI 0.65-0.80, p<0.0001).", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_915f5ab39161", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_3c3ac4b9", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": "https://takedapro.nl/node/737?customer_id=NL-TAK-P-0012400000d68qMAAQ&utm_source=smile&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=breacadd_continu&utm_term=fragmentvae&utm_content=hd21", "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [329.25, 382.5, 515.25, 531.75]}
{"kind": "visual", "role": "VISUAL_INFOGRAPHIC", "text": "An infographic presenting four key findings from ASCLEPIOS trials and post-hoc analyses of KESIMPTA treatment over 7 years, including NEDA-3 achievement rates, brain volume loss comparisons, MRI lesion suppression, and safety profile data.", "n": 1, "coverage": 0.1429, "window_months": 18, "first_seen": "2024-01", "source_id": "asset_88661000e506", "pattern_id": "uk_email_visual_infographic_5f26ad04", "visual_kind": "infographic", "image_url": null, "ocr_text": null, "classification": null, "page": 1, "bbox": [75.0, 827.9999389648438, 525.0, 1504.5]}
